<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,620,645]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[694,823,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis box="[694,823,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">A. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the head distinctly wider than long; the mandible wide apically and angulate; the clypeus with blunt median tooth; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the frons densely punctured; the circumocular suture present; the ocelli very small; the notaulus narrow; and the metapostnotum with the first metapostnotal carina and metapostnotal-propodeal sutures fused posteriorly, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[151,278,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis box="[151,278,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">A. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the head narrower; the mandible narrow, slightly angled, and with the lower tooth longer than others; the clypeus with an apical median tooth; the antennal scrobe carinate; the frons sparsely punctate; the circumocular suture absent; the ocelli small; and the metapostnotum with first the metapostnotal carina and metapostnotal-propodeal sutures convergent posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
